{"course":{"id":"challenger","name":"Spoken Waray for Retiring to Samar","description":"A practical, confidence-building Waray-Waray course designed for older adult expats settling in Daram, Samar, focusing on daily relations, market runs, and community connection.","dialect_base":"Standard Waray, Samar-leaning (Daram context)","level_range":"A0–B1","total_phases":7,"total_units":42,"design_notes":"Ordered by immediate survival and relationship needs. Grammatical concepts are introduced piecemeal using non-technical language. Markers unique to Samar (like 'in' and 'hin') are taught early as vocabulary-like elements rather than syntactic concepts to avoid overwhelming the mature adult learner."},"course_map":[{"phase_id":"p1","phase_title":"First Steps in Daram","units":[{"unit_id":"u1","title":"Greetings and Your Name"},{"unit_id":"u2","title":"Finding People and Saying Yes/No"},{"unit_id":"u3","title":"Your House and Family"},{"unit_id":"u4","title":"Asking for Food and Drink"},{"unit_id":"u5","title":"Counting and Buying Snacks"}]},{"phase_id":"p2","phase_title":"Daily Life in the Neighborhood","units":[{"unit_id":"u6","title":"Meeting the In-Laws"},{"unit_id":"u7","title":"Everyday Objects in the Yard"},{"unit_id":"u8","title":"Where are You Going? (Kain ka?)"},{"unit_id":"u9","title":"Talking About the Weather"},{"unit_id":"u10","title":"Time of Day and Simple Tasks"},{"unit_id":"u11","title":"Phase 2 Review & Celebration"}]},{"phase_id":"p3","phase_title":"Getting Around Town & Transport","units":[{"unit_id":"u12","title":"Taking a Tricycle"},{"unit_id":"u13","title":"Going by Boat (Baloto)"},{"unit_id":"u14","title":"Left, Right, Straight"},{"unit_id":"u15","title":"Finding the Church and Town Hall"},{"unit_id":"u16","title":"Landmarks"},{"unit_id":"u17","title":"Handling Small Delays"}]},{"phase_id":"p4","phase_title":"At the Market","units":[{"unit_id":"u18","title":"Sari-Sari Store Essentials"},{"unit_id":"u19","title":"Higher Numbers (1-20)"},{"unit_id":"u